***********************
0.	Introduction:
***********************

This file is for wizards of the domain Kalad. If you are new to 
the domain, reading this file should be one of the first things you do.

***************************
0.1	This file:
***************************

This file is rather long, and is full of rules, talk of demotion, and other
unpleasant topics. Nevertheless, in spite of all this is not meant to
intimidate you, but to help you find your way around in Genesis and Kalad.

It was put together drawing on the experience of helping other wizards into the
domain, with valuable contributions from these wizards. You, too, are
invited to comment on this file, to assist us improving it.

If you in the course of the next weeks come to a point where you tell yourself,
'This is stupid, they should have *told* me!', talk to the liege and suggest 
including a corresponding paragraph into this file. (Perhaps you should check
first if it is already included, and if it is, you might prefer not to tell 
the liege that you did not read this file properly. ;-))

***************************
0.2	Asking for help:
***************************

Most wizards, and all wizards in Kalad will help you if you have questions or
problems. It is preferable to ask a Kalad wizard or on the domain line first,
before asking an arch or on the wizline.


***************************
0.3	Rules:
***************************

The domain Kalad abides by all rules in the mud, written or unwritten!
The fact that one or more other domains might or might not do the same is
irrelvant as far as your coding for this domain is concerned. The main aim of
the domain is to produce interesting and balanced code.

There are many rules in Genesis, not all of the are written down. Therefore,
if you have a fantastic novel idea, ask someone more experienced first. You
might not be the first one, and it might be illegal.


***************************
0.4     The domain Kalad:
***************************

The land of Kalad is one where humans dominate, led by their patron
god, Thanar. Here, the demihuman races (elves, dwarves, gnomes, hobbits
and goblins) are rare and are more often known only through tales told
by the fireside. The populace is rampant with moral decay. Supposedly
good citizens allow slave operations in their city, and hold biased
attitudes to those not of their race. Evil, a force so obvious in other
lands, is rooted deep in the heart of many of the people. So much so, 
that evil men believe themselves to be good, when the opposite is true.

We aim towards creating areas where both evil and good players can
play - with a small bias towards the evil ones.

***************************
0.5	Introducing yourself:
***************************

To make yourself known to the other members of the domain, please post an
introductory note on the domain board. You should also post notes there
whenever you finish part of your project, so others can have a look at 
your code, or when you start working on a new project.

You should also add an entry with your name and current project in the file
/d/Kalad/doc/projects. If you need help with this, ask other members
of the domain.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


***************************
1.      Rules:
***************************

This is a summary of rules which you are required to follow. It is far from
comprehensive, but it should contain the most important ones.


1.1     Where to find them:

- Read the wiz scroll. If you do not have the scroll for some reason, type:
> clone /d/Genesis/obj/init_scroll
> read scroll

- Read the introductory files for wizards. You will find them by typing:
> man INTRO_RULES
> man GENESIS

- Read the rules for wizards in the directory /d/Genesis/doc/rules/wizard,
  especially the file wiz_vs_player_policy.

- Read the COPYRIGHT notice!
> more /doc/COPYRIGHT

- Re-read the rules file for mortals, read it from your now changed perspective!

- Read all the files in /d/Kalad/doc/ since you will find here some specific
  rules for you as a Kalad wizard.

- Read the weapon and armour guides (man weapon_guide, man armour_guide)


***************************
1.2	Opening code to mortals:
***************************

The Lord or the Lady is responsible for every object in the domain. Therefore,
he or she alone has the right to decide which new code is made available to the
mortals in the mud.

This means especially that a quest or an area may only be opened by the Lord or
the Lady of a domain, or by a wizard who has the explicit permission to do so.


***************************
1.3     What you should always keep in mind:
***************************

o  The game is over, you are a wizard!

   Interaction between your wizard character and mortals should be kept to a
   minimum.

   The following actions are illegal and can be punished by demotion:

   - Helping mortals in combat or with quests.

   - Giving hints to mortals, except general info about available commands.
     This means, hints will in most cases be just: 'read help topics'!

   - Restoring anything a mortal lost in a crash. That is for arches and the
     helpers of the player arch to do.

   - Helping a mortal in case of a bug, eg by transfering the player to another
     room, unless the mortal otherwise cannot continue to play. If a room has
     no exits due to a bug, and you know that it is not a trap, you may bring
     the mortal to a room closeby. Resetting a room so a mortal can finish a
     quest might be your last command as a wizard.

   - Giving a mortal any information on his or her character is in almost all
     cases illegal. This includes but is not restricted to telling stat values,
     skill values, fatigue values, weapon and armour classes and so on. It is
     not illegal to tell a mortal, 'If you want to know if that morning star is
     a club, why don't you appraise it?'

   - Your opinion on anything regarding the mud should not be discussed with
     mortals. This includes but is not limited to your opinion on the behaviour
     of mortals, on posts on boards that can be read by mortals, on the balance
     or imbalance of guilds, weapons, domains, and on the positive or negative
     sides of your fellow wizards.

     You should as a rule not post on boards open to mortals outside the domain
     Kalad. You should post on the wizard boards of other domains only if
     there is a valid reason to do so.


***************************
o Seconds:
***************************

   - If you have not finished your apprenticeship yet, as wizard of Kalad,
     you are not allowed to play with a second mortal character.

   - If you have finished your apprenticeship project, you may ask me for
     permission to play a mortal second character. As a rule I will not object
     if you have finished or made good progress on your second project.

   - You have to register your second character using the 'second' command.
     Failure to register your second will lead to the removal of both your
     wizard and your mortal character.

   - If you have a second character, do not interact with your two characters.
     Your second character ideally should not even know the solutions to quests
     your solved with the character that became a wizard! ;-)

   - Giving cash to a npc with your wizard character, and retrieving this later
     with your mortal character can lead to deletion of both characters.
     Reading up quest solutions with your wizard character so your mortal
     character can solve the quests, can lead to demotion.

   - Don't try to outthink me or admin in inventing ways how to help you second
     with your wizard character. If it will be of any help at all to your
     mortal character, chances are (and experience tells me) that it will be
     noticed by someone.

   - It is illegal to tell other mortals that your mortal character is the
     second of a wizard.

   - Your mortal second can NOT be a member of a guild council anywhere in the
     mud. Your mortal second should seek to keep a low profile, and if possible
     avoid direct conflicts with other players.

   - Your mortal second can NOT be a member of a layman or occupational guild
     that is within the domain of Kalad. You are allowed to join any race
     guilds in Kalad though.

   - If the identity of your second as the second of a wizard becomes known to
     mortals by whatever means, your second character will be erased. Since
     it is possible that the identity of your second character is revealed by
     means beyond your control, and mortal second of a wizard always lives
     under the threat of being erased. From personal experience, let me warn
     you to pay attention when you sign notes or letters.


***************************
1.4	Junior characters:
***************************

Junior characters are test characters that you can create to test code with a
mortal character. It is not legal to ask a mortal to test some code for you!

A mortal may come into contact only if the Lord or the Lady of the domain has
opened that code for contact with mortals!

If you have a Jr character, the same restrictions for interaction with mortals
apply as for your wizard character. 

Moreover, it is illegal to socialize with mortals using the Jr character. This
includes introducing the Jr character to other mortals. If you want to be
polite, move your Jr character to another room, and then explain the
circumstances to the mortals concerned using your wizard character.

More details on Jr characters can be found in 'man INTRO_RULES'.


***************************
1.5	Domain specific rules:
***************************


o  No toys!

   Every object in the domain must conform to the rules, including code not yet
   available to mortals. Weapons with WC 100 are illegal, even if they were
   meant just for your personal amusement.

o  Be careful in 'open' areas!

   Do not 'update' an object (including rooms!) in areas open to mortals,
   unless you know exactly what will happen when you do this, and that it will
   not interfere with any mortal.

   This means, that you should never update a room outside the domain Kalad,
   and inside only if you have read and understood the code!

   Use 'Call' extremely cautiously in areas open to mortals.

   Be certain that you know what you are doing, and that it will not interfere
   with mortals.


o  Check domain specific coding conventions and standards in the files in the
   directory /d/Kalad/doc/


***************************
1.6	Other wizards:
***************************

Be polite!

In specific:

o  It is considered to be polite to use the 'audience' command:

   > audience <name>

   to contact another wizard. Just transporting to the wizard with

   > goto <name>

   without asking if you are welcome is considered highly impolite. Look at
   the 'audience' command as knocking on a door before entering.

o  Try to keep questions to as small a group of wizards as appropriate. It
   makes little sense to bother a wizard of Krynn if you cannot find a file
   in Kalad.

   Use 'dtell' (or 'dtell Kalad') before you use 'wiz' if there are wizards
   of Kalad present.

   If someone takes the time to help you, especially if it is a wizard from
   another domain, please show that you appreciate that help.

o  Don't meddle in affairs that do not concern you.

   If you do not like code of another domain, you may - politely! - ask the
   responsible coder or the domain Lord or Lady if they are willing to discuss
   it with you.

   Do not complain on a board about it, especially not if it is a board that
   can be read by mortals.

   If you think the problem is serious, please talk to me first.

   If you discover a bug in another domain, make a bug report or mail the
   responsible coder or Lord/Lady. Do the same if you think an item is in
   violation of the rules. There is no need to involve the arches if a simple
   bug report will notify your colleagues of an oversight.

   In short, 'Don't do unto others what you do not want to be done unto you!'


***************************
1.7	Network security
***************************

A wizard character on a LPmud is a kind of super user.

You have been given this status because we trust you not to abuse this status.
This trust is personal, that means, it has been extended to you, not to anyone
else. We therefore expect you to take all reasonable precautions to prevent
anyone else to abuse the status of your wizard character.

One of these precautions consists of choosing a 'safe' password. If you do
not know what a 'safe' password is, please ask! If in doubt, please ask!

If you password is cracked, and someone else use your character, you will be
held responsible unless you can convince me that you were not negligent in
choosing a password.

Another of these precautions is that you keep your password secret and known
only to yourself. I will consider wizard who give their passwords away to
other persons, even to wizards of the domain Kalad and even to me, as
security risks to the domain and to Genesis.

If you want to keep your status as a wizard, do not give your password away
to anyone!

